article.headline: Oregon St. 62, S. Dakota 47
article.story: LUBBOCK, Texas -- Calvin Haynes and Roeland Schaftenaar had 14 points each to lead Oregon State to a 62-47 win over South Dakota at the Duel in the Desert tournament Saturday night. Daniel Deane added 10 points for Oregon State (1-1). South Dakota (0-2) was led by Louie Krogman, who had 11 points. Jake Thomas and Steve Smith added eight points each. The Coyotes kept it close early, trailing 16-13 midway through the first half after a basket by Kendall Cutler. But Oregon State ended the first half by outscoring South Dakota 16-8 over the final 10 minutes to take a 32-21 lead into halftime. Oregon State extended its lead to 47-28 seven minutes into the second half before the Coyotes went on a 15-3 run to climb as close as 50-43 with 5:18 left. But Beavers pulled away to extend the lead back to double digits and record the win.
